verbose_text: Similarly, Sun et al. 75 found positive results in 48 rabbits when osteochondral defects, created in the femoropatellar groove, were treated with a double centrifuged PRP product (800 rpm 15 minutes, 2000 rpm 15 minutes) in a polylactic-glycolic acid compared with those treated with polylactic-glycolic acid alone and those left untreated.
evidence: PRP product (800 rpm 15 minutes, 2000 rpm 15 minutes) in a polylactic-glycolic acid
